<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I don't know about you, but I understand Verant's Logic in that, "...playing the game in the preferred manner easier, safer, faster, or more profitable..." would decrease the fun. Let me share the logic Verant is using, since most people don't get it.<P>Think about this: What if all the enemies you had to kill were also extremely easy and more plentiful? Yes, you would make more money, until you realize that everyone else was making just as much more. Yes, you may net more experience, but only until you realize that everyone else was netting just as much more.<P>In the end, everyone will be growing at an accelerated rate, making your accomplishments mean no more than they did before the enhancements. The only difference: There would be very little challenge involved. The less you have to think, the more boring a task becomes. This means people will eventually get more bored, and will whine even more about "Camping SUCKS" and what not. This would put Verant right back at square one. Why do *anything* when this would be the end result?<P>I didn't say whether or not I agree with this; but Verant's logic is far from senseless once you really think in the long-term. <P>Just wanted to share that.  <IMG SRC="http://www.eqatlas.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Thillian (insert name here)<BR>20th Season Cleric, Bertoxxulous<BR>Proud member of the Alliance of the Stars
</FONT>
