<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Muse:<P>I have to completely disagree with your interpretation of Verant's (or Gordon's, not sure who's responsible for this position) logic.  What they're saying is "Doing a dungeon, as per our Vision, turned out to not be as rewarding as camping it, but still a heck of a lot more fun.  We have two choices to change this, either make camping less rewarding, or make 'doing' the dungeon more rewarding.  We don't like either of those choices.  We don't want to nerf camping, because some people like it, and we don't want to make 'doing' the dungeon easier, because that would make the game too easy."<P>I think this is totally reasonable.  A lot of times the most effective way to achieve a goal isn't necessarily the most fun.  You have to decide which is more important to you, the end goal, or the path to reaching it.<P>You can argue whether the game is too easy or not, but that's really a matter of personal preference.  No matter what Verant does, they're not going to please everybody.
</FONT>
