<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Gorgash wrote:<BR><B>A noble thought, but if it was made that easy for everyone then everyone in the game would be running around 60th level toons in planes gear just camping gods & dragons. That doesn't sound like much fun to me.</B><P>I don't necessarily believe that this is true.  I think that much of the fun of the game is being able to see the world from different perspectives and playing different characters.  I think a lot of the complaining on the big boards that "that class can do X better than me" is a side effect of the simple fact that *most* people are not going to be able to play multiple characters up to the 50's in level.  Of course they're mad, because they spent a ton of time playing a character that, in the long run, turned out to not be what they wanted to play, and now they're stuck with the thought of having to do it all over again.<P>Consider the alternative.  You can play to 50th in a few months of "regular" play time.  Given the amount of time I've put in (one char at 30th, two at 20th, multiple ones in early teens), I'd have a 55th lvl one and a few 40th level ones.  Everyone would have a stable of chars that they could pull out depending on their mood and where their friends wanted to hunt.<P>I think that if they made a few changes (level limits on weapon usage, most items no drop since they lack a better method to stop twinking, etc.), and made it so people could conceivably replay all the way through without maximum pain, then I think people would do it.  Then the servers wouldn't be so heavy with the super-powerful characters all the time, because those players would feel that they could spend their time playing a newbie without turning their back on months and months of time invested.  I know I would.<P>------------------<BR>Muse<BR>Bard and Cartographer
</FONT>
