<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I did read thru the posts here, however there is one thing I'm not clear on, and that is exactly what Verant considers the proper way to play the game.<P>My main characters are a lvl 25 druid and a lvl 24 ranger.  I started with the ranger but now mainly play the druid.  I probably played the ranger in the manner Verant deems appropriate, and I have played the druid by camping first the Orcs in EC, the Dervs in WC the Orcs in HH, the Aviaks in SK and now the Gnolls in SK in groups.  I find the game quite difficult and frustrating, and if I play in any other manner than described I end up losing levels and experience.<P>I understand that tweeking a game is a careful process and overall I think that most things about EQ are pretty well designed as far as classes, roleplaying, fighting, etc go.  I am after all extremely addicted to the game.  I think there are quite a few things wrong with the game in frame rate, cursor control, typing, transaction management, etc. but thats another story.  I don't propose any major changes in gaming, though I suspect that more variation in the spawn places and spawn times for coveted mobs would help.<P>One other thing I notice between my early ranger and later druid is I am loath to spend the time to develop any trade skills.  I have found that side of the game to be mind-numbingly boring, unprofitable financially, lacking as a source of pride, a waste of time compared to killing things, and hard on both my carpals and the tunnels they run thru.
</FONT>
