I want to be able to "do" a dungeon. I want to be able to explore new areas and lands. The only way to do these things is to level up to an appropiate level. The only efficient way, I've found, to level up is to camp. I don't like camping, alot of people don't. Camping is unrealistic and boring. With my first character I camped very little. It took me two months to reach level 7. I started a new one and with moderate camping I've reached level 8 in two weeks. Thats a big difference. There should be more balance. If I ever want to see Lady Vox, any of the planes, or even just another continent I'm going to have to do alot of camping. Why does there seem to be no alterative? I'm told there are 270,000 subscribers each paying $10 a month. With those kind of resources they should be able to figure something out.<BR>   On the EQ board I made a suggestion having to do with buffing quests in  a limited fashion. (follow Muse's link to Gordan's full post, if you have the interest, it's at the bottom) <BR>   Everquest is a great game with potential to be alot more. I pay my money gladly. But if/when I find another game that provides the same kind of fun without required camping I'll switch. I think I'll have plenty of company...   <BR>
