<HR size="1" color="#a62a2a">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Just a quick response to something someone said earlier. They stated that as a customer they should be more valuable to Verant because they only spend 6-10 hours a week playing as opposed to the people spending 60 hours a week playing, because they use less resources.<P>The alternative Verant could use if they wanted to is something Online RPGs in the past have done. They could always charge hourly. I remember playing Gemstone on Genie back in 94 when we had to pay 3.95 an hour to play the game. Just imagine what Everquest would be like if Verant charged even .99 an hour to play. It might seem to most people like "Oh, well now it will be balanced since people will only be able to play so much." But it brings in again another imbalance. If I make $65,000 a year and you are a kid in high school with a $20 a week allowance, won't it be unfair to you because you can't afford to pay what I can, thus taking RL issues and having them affect in game?<P>No way around it folks, no matter what Verant does they will adversely affect someone. By changing nothing they are merely protecting themselves. I can't say I agree with them, but I can understand why they do (or dont do) the things they do.<P>------------------<BR>Malex Diabhal<BR>51st Magician of Rodcet Nife
</FONT>
