<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
OK you hl people here is an idea from a newbie with TONS of old school D&D backgroud.  I hate camping.  To level you must do it.  I want to be able to do dungeons later in my life.  Here is an idea to stop the camping.  All creatures should remember their killers when they respawn.  If your 70% of the way into the dungeons and decide to camp there for the repeat loot, low and behold 40 or 50 mobs come knocking at your door with revenge on their mind.  Any character that stays within a given area for a certain amount of time could trigger this.  It would be so incredably annoying to fight off all the mobs that continuing to do the dungeon would be the only way to play it.  Also VI would obviously have to make doable dungeons also for this to happen.  As in the old days the green mobs would be on the first few levels, then work your way down to the red ones.  Then a boss type creature could be a few levels higher.  With this setup even very high level characters could not camp the "boss" creature for fear of the first 100 mobs they killed coming for them.  Even all green 100 vs 6 the way EQ is setup would make it advantege monster.  After the final kill and looting a one way dimentional door/lift/spell/ whatever could take you out.  Let me know what everyone thinks.<P>Azmodeous, cleric of 14th rank Xegony server.
</FONT>
